name: Fury Sliver
oracle_text: All Sliver creatures have double strike.
flavor_text:
"A rift opened, and our arrows were abruptly stilled. To move was to push the world. But the sliver's claw still twitched, red wounds appeared in Thed's chest, and ribbons of blood hung in the air."
—Adom Capashen, Benalish hero

name: Kor Outfitter
oracle_text: When Kor Outfitter enters the battlefield, you may attach target Equipment you control to target creature you control.
flavor_text: "We take only what we need to survive. Believe me, you will need this."

name: Siren Lookout
oracle_text:
Flying
When Siren Lookout enters the battlefield, it explores. (Reveal the top card of your library. Put that card into your hand if it's a land. Otherwise, put a +1/+1 counter on this creature, then put the card back or put it into your graveyard.)

name: Venerable Knight
oracle_text: When Venerable Knight dies, put a +1/+1 counter on target Knight you control.
flavor_text: "May this blade guide you on your great journey, as it did me on mine."

name: Wildcall
oracle_text: Manifest the top card of your library, then put X +1/+1 counters on it. (To manifest a card, put it onto the battlefield face down as a 2/2 creature. Turn it face up any time for its mana cost if it's a creature card.)
flavor_text: A howl on the wind hides many dangers.

name: Mystic Skyfish
oracle_text: Whenever you draw your second card each turn, Mystic Skyfish gains flying until end of turn.
flavor_text: The problem wasn't that fish had learned how to fly. It was that sharks had adapted to follow them.

name: Battlewing Mystic
oracle_text:
Kicker {R} (You may pay an additional {R} as you cast this spell.)
Flying
When Battlewing Mystic enters the battlefield, if it was kicked, discard your hand, then draw two cards.

name: Wall of Vipers
oracle_text:
Defender (This creature can't attack.)
{3}: Destroy Wall of Vipers and target creature it's blocking. Any player may activate this ability.
flavor_text:
What wall can never be climbed, but is always scaled?
—Nakaya riddle

name: Whiptongue Hydra
oracle_text:
Reach
When Whiptongue Hydra enters the battlefield, destroy all creatures with flying. Put a +1/+1 counter on Whiptongue Hydra for each creature destroyed this way.
flavor_text:
"Where'd all the birds go?"
—Kaldrin, jungle sightseer

name: Wall of Roots
oracle_text:
Defender
Put a -0/-1 counter on Wall of Roots: Add {G}. Activate only once each turn.
flavor_text: Root systems in Mwonvuli twist through currents of mana rather than soil.

name: Blood Operative
oracle_text:
Lifelink
When Blood Operative enters the battlefield, you may exile target card from a graveyard.
Whenever you surveil, if Blood Operative is in your graveyard, you may pay 3 life. If you do, return Blood Operative to your hand.

oracle_text: Parley — When Selvala's Enforcer enters the battlefield, each player reveals the top card of their library. For each nonland card revealed this way, put a +1/+1 counter on Selvala's Enforcer. Then each player draws a card.

name: Fresh Meat

flavor_text: A scavenger's favorite appetizer is death.

oracle_text:
Orzhov Guildgate enters the battlefield tapped.
{T}: Add {W} or {B}.
flavor_text: Enter to find wealth, security, and eternal life . . . for just a small price up front.

name: Charge
oracle_text: Creatures you control get +1/+1 until end of turn.
flavor_text:
"Honor rides before us. All we have to do is catch up."
—Danitha Capashen

oracle_text:
Defender (This creature can't attack.)
As long as Novice Knight is enchanted or equipped, it can attack as though it didn't have defender.
flavor_text: Even the greatest hero begins with nothing.

name: Afflict
oracle_text:

Hexproof (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities your opponents control.)
